const markdown: string =
  "**Access all apprenticeship job opportunities available across France for free of charge and in real-time.** The returned job opportunities are those collected by [La bonne alternance](https://labonnealternance.apprentissage.beta.gouv.fr/) and [its partner sites](https://mission-apprentissage.notion.site/Liste-des-partenaires-de-La-bonne-alternance-3e9aadb0170e41339bac486399ec4ac1?pvs=74).\n\nThree types of job opportunities are available :\n\n1. **offres_emploi_lba** : job postings submitted directly via our job posting platform (25,000 postings in 2025).\n\n2. **offres_emploi_partenaires** : job postings sourced from our partnerships with companies such as Enedis and Engie, from recruitment platforms such as Hellowork, Meteojob, and France Travail, as well as from multiposters like Talentplug and Veritone, and ATS systems such as Kelio or Wink ([see our partner list](https://mission-apprentissage.notion.site/Liste-des-partenaires-de-La-bonne-alternance-3e9aadb0170e41339bac486399ec4ac1?pvs=74)). Approximately 320,000 job postings were distributed in 2025.\n\n3. **recruteurs_lba** : companies identified as having strong hiring potential but that have not posted job offers; we encourage candidates to submit unsolicited applications.\n\n**💡Some tips for your integrations:**\n\n- You can search for all job opportunities using the following criteria: ROME code(s), RNCP, geolocation, diploma level, and search radius.\n- For offres_emploi_lba: it is possible to distinguish between job postings published directly by companies and those published by training centers recruiting on behalf of partner companies, thanks to the “is_delegated” field. If this field is set to TRUE, the posting comes from a training center.\n- For offres_emploi_partenaires: the “Partner Label” field allows you to identify which job postings to include or exclude depending on your needs.\n\nResults are returned by source priority (La bonne alternance then its partners), by increasing distance to the search location if it has been provided as a parameter, and by decreasing creation date.\n\n**📥You can also download all job postings in JSON format using [this endpoint](/fr/documentation-technique#tag/Offre-Emploi/operation/jobsExport).**\n\nThe use of this API is free and restrictied to non-profit uses. Note that any use of this data for commercial purposes, such as reselling or billing access to third parties such as candidates, companies, or schools, is prohibited.\n";
